"新的DomU客户机虚拟机在一个文件中定义。一些特定的定义，如名称、键映射和VNC连接详细信息也被定义。以下是一个最小的DomU配置示例的[.filename]#freebsd.cfg#文件内容："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:998
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cat freebsd.cfg\n"
"builder = \"hvm\" <.>\n"
"name = \"freebsd\" <.>\n"
"memory = 1024 <.>\n"
"vcpus = 2 <.>\n"
"vif = [ 'mac=00:16:3E:74:34:32,bridge=bridge0' ] <.>\n"
"disk = [\n"
"'/dev/zvol/tank/xendisk0,raw,hda,rw', <.>\n"
"'/root/freebsd.iso,raw,hdc:cdrom,r' <.>\n"
"  ]\n"
"vnc = 1 <.>\n"
"vnclisten = \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
"serial = \"pty\"\n"
"usbdevice = \"tablet\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1001
#, fuzzy
msgid "These lines are explained in more detail:"
msgstr "这些行会被更详细地解释："

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1010
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<.> This defines what kind of virtualization to use. `hvm` refers to "
"hardware-assisted virtualization or hardware virtual machine. Guest "
"operating systems can run unmodified on CPUs with virtualization extensions,"
" providing nearly the same performance as running on physical hardware. "
"`generic` is the default value and creates a PV domain.  <.> Name of this "
"virtual machine to distinguish it from others running on the same Dom0. "
"Required.  <.> Quantity of RAM in megabytes to make available to the VM. "
"This amount is subtracted from the hypervisor's total available memory, not "
"the memory of the Dom0.  <.> Number of virtual CPUs available to the guest "
"VM. For best performance, do not create guests with more virtual CPUs than "
"the number of physical CPUs on the host.  <.> Virtual network adapter. This "
"is the bridge connected to the network interface of the host. The `mac` "
"parameter is the MAC address set on the virtual network interface. This "
"parameter is optional, if no MAC is provided Xen(TM) will generate a random "
"one.  <.> Full path to the disk, file, or ZFS volume of the disk storage for"
" this VM. Options and multiple disk definitions are separated by commas.  "
"<.> Defines the Boot medium from which the initial operating system is "
"installed. In this example, it is the ISO image downloaded earlier. Consult "
"the Xen(TM) documentation for other kinds of devices and options to set.  "
"<.> Options controlling VNC connectivity to the serial console of the DomU. "
"In order, these are: active VNC support, define IP address on which to "
"listen, device node for the serial console, and the input method for precise"
" positioning of the mouse and other input methods. `keymap` defines which "
"keymap to use, and is `english` by default."
msgstr ""
"<.> 这定义了使用的虚拟化类型。`hvm` 是硬件辅助虚拟化或硬件虚拟机的缩写。客户操作系统可以在支持虚拟化扩展的 CPU 上无修改地运行，在性能上几乎与在物理硬件上运行相同。`generic` 是默认值，创建一个 PV 域。\n"
"<.> 虚拟机的名称，用于区分在同一 Dom0 上运行的其他虚拟机。必填项。\n"
"<.> 分配给虚拟机的内存数量，以兆字节为单位。此数量从超级管理程序的总可用内存中减去，并不会减少 Dom0 的内存。\n"
"<.> 客户虚拟机可用的虚拟 CPU 数量。为了获得最佳性能，请勿创建使用超过主机上物理 CPU 数量的虚拟 CPU 的客户。\n"
"<.> 虚拟网络适配器。这是连接到主机的网络接口的桥接器。`mac` 参数是设置在虚拟网络接口上的 MAC 地址。如果没有提供 MAC 地址，会使用 Xen(TM) 生成一个随机的 MAC 地址。\n"
"<.> 此虚拟机的磁盘、文件或 ZFS 卷的完整路径。选项和多个磁盘定义使用逗号分隔。\n"
"<.> 定义引导介质，用于安装初始操作系统。在此示例中，是之前下载的 ISO 镜像。请查阅 Xen(TM) 文档以了解其他设备和设置选项。\n"
"<.> 控制与 DomU 的串口控制台的 VNC 连接的选项。按顺序分别为：激活 VNC 支持、定义要监听的 IP 地址、串口控制台的设备节点和精确定位鼠标和其他输入方法的输入方式。`keymap` 定义要使用的键盘映射，默认为英文。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1012
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"After the file has been created with all the necessary options, the DomU is "
"created by passing it to `xl create` as a parameter."
msgstr "在使用所有必要选项创建文件之后，通过将其作为参数传递给 `xl create`，可以创建 DomU。"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1016
#, no-wrap
msgid "# xl create freebsd.cfg\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1025
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Each time the Dom0 is restarted, the configuration file must be passed to "
"`xl create` again to re-create the DomU.  By default, only the Dom0 is "
"created after a reboot, not the individual VMs.  The VMs can continue where "
"they left off as they stored the operating system on the virtual disk.  The "
"virtual machine configuration can change over time (for example, when adding"
" more memory).  The virtual machine configuration files must be properly "
"backed up and kept available to be able to re-create the guest VM when "
"needed."
msgstr ""
"每次重新启动 Dom0 时，必须重新传递配置文件给 `xl create` 以重新创建 DomU。默认情况下，在重新启动后只会创建 "
"Dom0，而不会创建各个虚拟机。虚拟机可以继续运行，因为它们将操作系统存储在虚拟磁盘中。虚拟机的配置可以随着时间的推移而发生变化（例如，当添加更多内存时）。虚拟机的配置文件必须妥善备份并保持可用，以便在需要时重新创建虚拟机。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1028
#, fuzzy
msgid "The output of `xl list` confirms that the DomU has been created."
msgstr "`xl list`命令的输出确认了DomU已经创建成功。"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1035
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# xl list\n"
"Name                                        ID   Mem VCPUs      State   Time(s)\n"
"Domain-0                                     0  8192     4     r-----  1653.4\n"
"freebsd                                      1  1024     1     -b----   663.9\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1042
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"To begin the installation of the base operating system, start the VNC "
"client, directing it to the main network address of the host or to the IP "
"address defined on the `vnclisten` line of [.filename]#freebsd.cfg#.  After "
"the operating system has been installed, shut down the DomU and disconnect "
"the VNC viewer.  Edit [.filename]#freebsd.cfg#, removing the line with the "
"`cdrom` definition or commenting it out by inserting a `+#+` character at "
"the beginning of the line.  To load this new configuration, it is necessary "
"to remove the old DomU with `xl destroy`, passing either the name or the id "
"as the parameter.  Afterwards, recreate it using the modified "
"[.filename]*freebsd.cfg*."
msgstr ""
"要开始安装基本操作系统，请启动VNC客户端，将其指向主机的主网络地址或在[.filename]#freebsd.cfg#的`vnclisten`行上定义的IP地址。操作系统安装完成后，关闭DomU并断开VNC查看器的连接。编辑[.filename]#freebsd.cfg#，删除包含`cdrom`定义的行，或在该行开头插入一个`+#+`字符进行注释。要加载这个新配置，需要使用`xl"
" destroy`命令删除旧的DomU，并传递名称或ID作为参数。然后，使用修改后的[.filename]*freebsd.cfg*重新创建它。"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1047
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# xl destroy freebsd\n"
"# xl create freebsd.cfg\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/virtualization/_index.adoc:1051
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The machine can then be accessed again using the VNC viewer.  This time, it "
"will boot from the virtual disk where the operating system has been "
"installed and can be used as a virtual machine."
msgstr "接下来可以使用 VNC Viewer 再次访问该机器。这一次，它将从已安装操作系统的虚拟磁盘启动，并可用作虚拟机。"

